          <h2>Update on PNA Bylaws Changes</h2>
          <p dir="ltr">Our previous newsletter shared three proposed bylaws changes. Upon further review of the bylaws, the board found additional changes that need to be made to reflect some of the realities of how we can efficiently function as a delivery center. This will be a multi-step process, beginning with this notification to members.<br>
            <br>
            Our bylaws were written and approved by NYCON (New York Council of Non Profits, Inc.) when we were founded. Below are proposed changes. We have included the relevant text from the bylaws and we have struck through the text we are proposing to change. Our proposed language is in red ink. &nbsp;We have also added a short explanation of why each change is necessary.<br>
            <br>
            Please consider the five proposed changes below and send any comments to the PNA Administrator at <a href="mailto:info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org?subject=Comments%20on%20bylaws" target="_blank" style="color: #24b3e3;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: none;">info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.or</a>g by November 19 so that the board can review all comments from current PNA members before voting. After that, members will vote on the board-approved changes.<br>
            <br>
            1. <strong>Change all references to British Canoe Union and BCU</strong> to British Canoeing and BC. (This reflects the organization&rsquo;s current name and acronym.)<br>
            <br>
            <span>2. </span><strong>Article 7: Nomination of Directors</strong><br>
            <span>The nominating committee will consist of a chair and at least two other members. </span><strike>It will be elected during the annual meeting of the board from a slate presented by the Executive Committee.</strike> <span style="color:#FF0000">The board will appoint a nominating committee whose role is to publicize the board member criteria, solicit nominations and short biographical statements, and&nbsp; present the names and bios to the board. The board will carry out the election during the two weeks leading up to the annual meeting.</span> The nominating committee will elect its own chair. The nominating committee shall make every effort to seek out qualified candidates to ensure, as much as possible, that the Board comprises a diverse representation of PNA membership. <strike>The Nominating Committee will can function during the entire year in seeking and recommending candidates for positions on the Board or as Officers. The Nominating Committee will present recommendations to the board regarding any interim vacancy on the Board, or in any Officer&#39;s position, that may occur. The Board will consider the nominations of the Nominating Committee and any other nominee recommended by Board members. The Nominating Committee is responsible to contact Directors absent from two consecutive Board meetings to ascertain whether circumstances prevent their further service from on the Board and to recommend to the Board whether such Directors should be removed from the Board.</strike><br>
            <br>
            <strong><span>Why are we seeking this change?</span></strong><br>
            <span>This provides clarity about our existing process.</span><br>
            <span>Interim vacancies are addressed by </span>Article 6.6 and 6.7<br>
            <span>Board absences are addressed in the </span>PNA Board Member Attendance Policy. &nbsp;<br>
            <br>
            3. <strong>Change all references to Regional Coaching Offices or RCOs</strong> to Regional Representatives. (This reflects current terminology.)<br>
            <br>
            <strong>4. Section 5.1. Annual Meeting</strong><br>
            The annual meeting of PNA membership for such business as may properly come before it shall be held <strike>no earlier than the first week of October and not later than the last week in November of each year</strike> i<span style="color:#FF0000">n the first quarter of the year </span>at the time and place to be decided by the Board of Directors. Notice of the annual meeting and all other meetings of the members shall be via PNA website at least fifteen (15) days prior to the date of such meeting. Five (5) shall constitute a quorum at the Annual Meeting. <strike>In the event a quorum is not present at the meeting, the election shall be submitted to a vote of the general membership.</strike><br>
            <br>
            <strong>Why are we seeking this change?</strong><br>
            A first quarter meeting is a better&nbsp;fit with the industry cycle.<br>
            Most voting is done electronically in advance of the annual meeting.<br>
            <br>
            <strong>5. Section 6.6. Terms of Office</strong><br>
            The Board of Directors shall enter into their term of office <strike>seven days after the close of the election.</strike> <span style="color:#FF0000">upon the beginning of the calendar year following their election</span>. Directors and Officers shall hold office for two years and may succeed in that office until a successor is elected and qualified, unless having earlier lost the status of a Director. <span style="color:#FF0000">In order to stagger terms, at the 2018 election, the top vote-getter will get to choose a one-year or two-year term, the second highest vote-getter will choose next and so on until half the newly elected directors have one-year terms and half have two-year terms. </span>All board members can nominate themselves for reelection in subsequent years, and all subsequent elections will be for two-year terms. &nbsp;In the event of the resignation or removal of any Board member, the Board has the power to fill vacancies in the Board and its officers for the remainder unexpired terms and act for its interests in any way not inconsistent with these Bylaws. The immediate past President shall serve in an advisory capacity for an additional one-year term upon expiration of her/his term of office if it coincides with the expiration of her/his term on the Board. The immediate Past-Chair shall serve as an adviser to the current Chair.<br>
            <br>
            <strong>Why are we seeking this change?</strong><br>
            To reflect the date of the annual meeting and elections.<br>
            &nbsp;</p>
