            <h2>PNA/BC Annual Orientation/Moderation Event</h2>
            <p>Dates: January 21-25, 2018</p>
            <p>Location: Charleston Parks and Recreation, James Island County Park, Charleston, SC 29412</p>
            <p>PNA is excited to announce the first of its kind Coach Orientation and Moderation event to happen in North America. This is an exciting time as PNA is finally on track to conform to the standards of all BC Home Nations. This event is designed to orient new providers to deliver the new Coach Award (old Level 2), orient new providers to deliver the new Paddlesport Leader Award, and orient new providers to deliver the Foundation Safety and Rescue Training course.</p>
            <p>As well, Current Leadership Providers (old 4 and 5 Star) are required to participate in a moderation event prior to December 31, 2018 to assure everyone agrees as to the standards that these courses need to be trained and assessed. Current Foundation Safety and Rescue Training (FSRT) Providers need to be moderated for the same reasons, again before December 31, 2018.</p>
            <p>PNA&#39s Coaching Group has identified a need for these events to take place and has scheduled an event to take place when BC Trainers are available and in a location that has the necessary infrastructure to assure the tradition of a PNA/BC annual orientation/moderation event starts off the best possible.</p>
            <h3>Schedule of Events and Description</h3>
            <p>Jan 21: Moderate Water Leader Provider Moderation- this is a one day event for current 4 and 5 Star Providers. Maximum of 6 participants per trainer. *Maximum 12 participants.</p>
            <p>Jan 22-23: An orientation to begin the process of becoming a Provider for the new Coach Award. This is a two-day event. Maximum 12 participants.</p>
            <p>Jan 24: Paddlesport Leader Provider Moderation- this is a one day event. Maximum of 8 participants per trainer. *Maximum 16 participants.</p>
            <p>Jan 25: FSRT Moderation/Orientation- this is a one day event. Maximum of 8 participants per trainer. This will be run as both an orientation and moderation simultaneously. *Maximum 16 participants.</p>
            <p>Cost for the training is $150/day. Participants will be responsible for their own lodging costs (PNA will be reserving cabins at the Park), meals, transportation to Charleston, and boat rental, if necessary.</p>
            <p>To participate in either the Coach Provider orientation or the Paddlesport Leader Provider orientation there is an application process. Please see below for application details.</p>
            <p>Once your application has been accepted you may register for the trainings by emailing <a href="mailto:info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org" target="_blank">Scott Fairty, PNA Administrator</a></p>
            <p>FSRT and Leadership Provider Moderation trainings are on a first come basis, so register early. To register contact <a href="mailto:info@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org" target="_blank">Scott Fairty, PNA Administrator</a></p>
            <p>For more information about the Park: <a href="https://www.ccprc.com/1729/Camping-Lodging" target="_blank">James Island County Park</a></p>
            <p>For further information about the event contact <a href="mailto:coaching@paddlesportsnorthamerica.org" target="_blank">PNA&#39s Coaching Group</a> or your <a href="http://www.paddlesportsnorthamerica.org/about#regional-reps" target="_blank">Regional Representative</a>.</p>
            <p>*Two trainers will be available to run concurrent sessions if needed.</p>
